membership:
- Within the framework of the European Union, we manage the Technical Secretariat of the ‘European Network on Social Inclusion and Roma under the Structural Funds’ (EURoma Network)&#xd;
- In the Spanish context, we form part of the following consultative bodies, networks and alliances:&#xd;
Spanish State Council of Social Action NGOs&#xd;
Spanish State Council of the Roma People&#xd;
Spanish Council for the Promotion of Equal Treatment and Non-Discrimination of Persons on Grounds of Race or Ethnicity&#xd;
&#xd;
- The FSG is actively involved in Spanish networks and partnerships to build momentum in civil society for the promotion of the Roma community through mutual exchange and joint actions:&#xd;
Spanish Platform of Social Action NGOs (POAS)&#xd;
Spanish Platform of Third Sector (PTS)&#xd;
European Anti-Poverty Network in Spain (EAPN-ES) at both central and regional levels.&#xd;
Spanish Association of Foundations&#xd;
Spanish Association of Fundraising&#xd;
Platform for the Management of Diversity by Police Forces&#xd;
Lealtad Foundation (on Transparency)&#xd;
Institute for the Quality of NGOs (ICONG)&#xd;
The informal but highly consolidated informal network created by the FSG with the other social organisations of the Operational Programme Fight Against Discrimination/ Operational Programme Social Inclusion and Social Economy (Cáritas, Cruz Roja española and Fundación Once).&#xd;
Social Inclusion Network of Spain&#xd;
Network of the Fight against Early School Leaving and Training&#xd;
Forum of Society on Drugs (National Plan on Drugs, Spanish Ministry of Health, Social Services and Equality)&#xd;
Healthy Leisure Group (National Plan on Drugs)&#xd;
Youth Council of Spain

memberOrga:
FSG as such is a foundation and therefore has no members.  &#xd;
&#xd;
If we refer to the EURoma Network (of which FSG is Technical Secretariat), it involves representatives from public authorities, notably Managing Authorities (mainly ESF) and National Roma Contact Points, from 15 Member States. see www.euromanet.eu
